articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Tesla (TSLA.O) will build a 25,000-euro ($26,837.50) car at its factory near Berlin, a source with knowledge of the matter said on Monday, in a long-awaited development for the electric vehicle maker which is aiming for mass uptake of its cars.
articles.title: Tesla to build 25,000-euro car at German plant - source

articles.author: Maha Dahan, Olesya Astakhova
articles.description: Top oil exporters Saudi Arabia and Russia confirmed on Sunday they would continue with their additional voluntary oil output cuts until the end of the year as concerns over demand and economic growth continue to weigh on crude markets.
articles.title: Saudi Arabia, Russia to continue additional voluntary oil cuts

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China's attempts to keep the yuan from falling contributed to last week's chaos in money markets, sources involved say, pointing to the pressure behind the scenes as Beijing tries to guide its economy and markets through a major slowdown.
articles.title: Exclusive: China's clashing priorities behind rare money market distress

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China recorded its first-ever quarterly deficit in foreign direct investment (FDI), according to balance of payments data, underscoring Beijing's challenge in wooing overseas companies in the wake of a "de-risking" move by Western governments.
articles.title: China's first deficit in foreign investment signals West's 'de-risking' pressure

articles.author: Julia Payne
articles.description: A major pharmaceutical rules overhaul, proposed by the European Commission in April, could see Europe's share in global research and development contract by a third to 21% by 2040 translating to 2 billion euros ($2.15 billion) per year in lost investment, industry group EFPIA said on Monday.
articles.title: EU proposal may accelerate pharma innovation decline, industry group says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Elon Musk's artificial intelligence startup xAI will be integrated into his social media platform X and also be available as a standalone app, he said on Sunday in a post.
articles.title: Musk to integrate xAI with social media platform X

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Barclays said it now expects the U.S. Federal Reserve to deliver a 25 basis point interest rate increase in January instead of an earlier expectation for a December hike.
articles.title: Barclays sees Fed raising rate in January instead of December

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Efforts to pressure Israel to spare civilians in Gaza were set to continue on Monday after Israel rebuffed calls for a ceasefire amid a U.S. diplomatic blitz to the region to help contain escalation of the conflict.
articles.title: Pressure on Israel over civilians steps up as ceasefire calls rebuffed

articles.author: Sheila Dang
articles.description: Social media researchers have canceled, suspended or changed more than 100 studies about X, formerly Twitter, as a result of actions taken by Elon Musk that limit access to the social media platform, nearly a dozen interviews and a survey of planned projects show.
articles.title: Exclusive: Elon Musk's X restructuring curtails disinformation research, spurs legal fears

articles.author: Ryan Woo
articles.description: Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese stopped by Beijing's Temple of Heaven on Monday as he followed in the footsteps of the first Australian leader to visit China, retracing a walk made five decades ago as ties were being established.
articles.title: Australia's Albanese retraces historic Beijing walk on visit to mend ties
